  "prompt": "How to add a link in a Quora answer to another Quora answer when using Quora iPhone app?",
  "response": "To add a link to another Quora answer while using the Quora iPhone app, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Find the Answer to Link to:**\n   - Open the Quora app on your iPhone.\n   - Navigate to the answer you'd like to link to.\n   - Tap the share icon (usually an arrow pointing upwards or outwards). This will generate a URL link to that specific answer.\n\n2. **Copy the Link:**\n   - Once you tap the share icon, a menu will appear with options like \"Copy Link,\" \"Share via,\" etc.\n   - Select \"Copy Link\" to copy the answer's URL to your clipboard.\n\n3. **Go to Your Answer or Create a New Answer:**\n   - Now, navigate to the question where you want to add your answer, or go to your already existing answer if you're editing.\n   - Tap on the text box where you write your answer.\n\n4. **Insert the Link:**\n   - Type your response as you normally would.\n   - When you need to insert the link, press and hold the location in the text where you want to place the link.\n   - In the text box, tap again and the option to \u201cPaste\u201d should appear. Tap on \u201cPaste\u201d to insert the URL.\n\n5. **Format the Link (Optional but Recommended):**\n   - You can create a cleaner look rather than pasting the raw URL. To do this, write the text you want to display (e.g., \u201cCheck out this answer\u201d).\n   - Then, highlight this text by selecting it.\n   - Tap the format (usually a toolbar appears above the keyboard with options like bold, italics, link, etc.).\n   - Select the link icon and paste the URL into the dialog box that appears.\n\n6. **Complete Your Answer:**\n   - Finish writing your response and review it to ensure the link is correct and properly formatted.\n   - Once satisfied, submit your answer.\n\nBy linking to other answers in your response, you can provide more value and additional context for readers, helping them navigate related content effectively on the Quora platform.",
